children.subject: I am currently in the class and they honestly do not expect people to have completed all of the requirements. Most people haven't taken ee120 for example. I would say 16b lab is a great intro and 61c knowledge is nice for the sake of knowing how the microprocessor works, but solid coding knowledge and a willingness to put in the time for lab is the most crucial. The lab is self directed with weekly checkpoints and the TAs are great. There are only about ~30 people in the class and a mix of backgrounds so I would say the requirements are somewhat soft. The main thing is knowing how to code and use a debugger ( we use C in this class, but not advanced stuff) and have a basic understanding of circuits.

history.content:
I am planning to EE 192 next spring, and I am wondering what classes I should take to prepare for EE 192 next semester.

The Prerequisites for EE 192 is listed as:
EECS 16A, EECS 16B, COMPSCI 61A, COMPSCI 61B, COMPSCI 61C, and EL ENG 120.

I am pretty sure that this is the minimum requirement. 
What are the other classes I should take to prepare for EE 192?

Thank you!
